Data Scientist		Bloomberg LP		Princeton, NJ, USA		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><strong>Job Requisition Number:</strong>46818<br /><br />The Role:<br /><br />Show us what you can do! The Bloomberg Data Sciences Group is looking for skilled data scientists. Maybe you have been working with geospatial data or bioinformatics data and would like to move to the next level? Perhaps you are a quant who has stayed current and now would like to move ahead to the world of Big Data. We need your expertise to solve complex business questions. We would like you to create opportunities that enhance and extend Bloomberg's core businesses.<br /><br />In this exciting role, you will design, create, implement, and manage predictive analytics that leverage large and varied datasets, both financial and non-financial, using a wide range of analytical tools, methods, and platforms. You will be leading projects where your interests and enthusiasm will have a major impact on business direction. Come help us build the future!<br /><br />This role will challenge your business skills, too. You will be expected to identify areas of interest to the business, recognize which models and concepts should be applied to the business problem, and then help the team acquire the data resources. You will create and implement those models. You will also mentor and assist the junior members of the team. You will guide their work and contribute to the overall team's accomplishments. An open, creative approach is critical to your success!<br /><br />Having an advanced degree is fantastic, but does not necessarily constitute that a candidate would be qualified for this role. For a candidate to be qualified, they need to have professional work history in addition to any post-doc research completed after earning advanced education. A strong business acumen, and ability to recognize ROI, is essential to success in this role.<br /><br />Responsibilities:<br /><br />- Design lean proofs of concepts (POC) to answer targeted business questions. Explore and work with a wide range of proprietary, interesting data stores. Apply existing methods or develop new methods. Be creative!<br />- You will be relied upon for technical leadership in this role. We need the best and brightest!<br />- Engage in data analysis in a practical way. Convince business leaders that your results are worth investing in. Be innovative!<br />- Collaborate with Bloomberg's advanced visualization team. Be colorful!<br />-Educate other analysts and business team members. Be generous!<br /><br />Required Qualifications:<br /><br />- Advanced Degree in Statistics, Math, Engineering, Physical Sciences (Biology, Chemistry, Physics, etc.), Computer Science or another quantitative discipline.<br />- 5 - 7 years of experience in the use of advanced statistical analysis/machine learning methods in a professional working environment.<br />- A minimum of 3 years of financial services specific experience is required for this role.<br />- Strong understanding of core financial concepts.<br /><br />Preferred Skills:<br /><br />- Experience with mapping business needs to a data science solution.<br />- Fluent in modern advanced analytical tools (e.g. Python, R, MATLAB etc.).<br />- Substantial experience with the use of relational databases for data storage<br />- Experience using SQL for data extraction and management (MSSQL, Oracle, MySQL).<br />- Knowledge of NoSQL data stores, MapReduce and software frameworks like Hadoop.<br />- Must be able to address multiple priorities in an extremely fast-paced environment.<br /><br /></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Bloomberg, the global business and financial information and news leader, gives influential decision makers a critical edge by connecting them to a dynamic network of information, people and ideas. The companyâs strength â delivering data, news and analytics through innovative technology, quickly and accurately â is at the co